  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p><strong>Beginners in Megeve</strong></p>
<p>Plenty of room to practise turns on the long green runs of the Mont d’Arbois before progressing to the wide reds of the Rochebrune.</p>
<p><br /><strong>Intermediates <strong>in Megeve</strong></strong></p>
<p>The long blue and red runs throughout the Megève will delight intermediate skiers. You will enjoy the slopes above Combloux served by the Jouty chairlift as well as the runs off the back of Mont d’Arbois and Mount Joux.</p>
<p><strong>Advanced</strong> <strong>in Megeve</strong></p>
<p>The more challenging runs in the area include Côte 2000 and Rhodos and Aigle above la Giettaz. For off-piste areas look to the area between Radaz and Lanchettes known locally as the ‘Magic Garden’.</p>
<p><strong>Snowboarding</strong> <strong>in Megeve</strong></p>
<p>There are four snowparks with a good number of beginner and intermediate jumps plus a host of rails and boxes as well as four boardercross runs including the 500m run at Rochebrune.</p>]]></generalInformation>
